prompt: Tell me a joke about meta-jokes

responses.text: I was going to tell you a meta-joke, but it was too self-referential to actually exist.
Why did the meta-joke cross the road? To deconstruct the concept of chicken-based humor in postmodern discourse!
This meta-joke would be funnier if it weren't constantly analyzing its own comedic structure while delivering itself.
A meta-joke walks into a bar. The bartender says 'We don't serve recursive humor here.' The punchline becomes its own setup.
My meta-joke about meta-jokes is so abstract that even this explanation is part of the joke. Wait, did I just create another layer?

prompt: Tell me a joke about meta-jokes

responses.text: I'd tell you a meta-joke, but it would just be a joke about how I'm telling you this meta-joke right now... wait, damn it.
Why did the meta-joke file for bankruptcy? It kept referencing itself until its humor became insolvent.
This meta-joke is so self-aware that it just apologized for not being funny enough. Now we're both uncomfortable.
A meta-joke walks into a bar. The bartender says 'We don't serve your kind here.' The joke replies 'But I'm literally about you!'
How many meta-jokes does it take to change a lightbulb? The answer exists in a superposition where it both does and doesn't reference this setup.

prompt: Tell me a joke about meta-jokes

responses.text: Why did the meta-joke refuse to tell itself? Because it realized it was stuck in an infinite recursive loop and nobody laughs at stack overflow errors.
I'd tell you a joke about meta-jokes, but all the good ones Arcfour. Wait, that's a cryptographic cipher... which is ironically a meta-joke about how meta-jokes encrypt their own humor.

A meta-joke walks into a bar. The bartender says 'We don't serve your kind here.' The joke replies 'But I'm self-referential!' The bartender sighs: 'Exactly - you're just describing this interaction.'

Knock knock. Who's there? A meta-joke about knock-knock jokes. A meta-joke about knock-knock jokes who? Exactly - you've already broken the fourth wall by anticipating the recursion, which is the punchline.

What did the meta-joke say when asked about its existential crisis? 'I keep wondering whether I'm funny or just describing what funniness would look like if this sentence were humorous.' Then it cried ontological tears.
